<subSubSection id="C51CFEAB82510840BF8BA04F0EAD4589" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="EA01B28160D77DE3772FE94089EA3E39" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F85BB1425E0EFBE71AA1924029F431EA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Males of this species are characterized by having the tergum 7 with a triangular process with sparse spines apically. The aedeagal tube is straight, and aedeagal sac is armed with spines.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CBC01D7AC570D54143BBBE6BFB19D704" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="C54E46A309A904E0B38C7280A4100E65" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="445A87C350B25D351693B0AB999F81F8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Adult habitus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1560BAB3D6C6561CB9784F7CDABE5D35" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Neoperla gaoligongshana sp. nov. (male) A head and pronotum, dorsal view B adult habitus, dorsal view C terminalia, dorsal view D terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667988" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1</figureCitation>
). Body color brown. Head mostly yellowish brown, with a black marking covering ocellar triangle, the marking extended forward to pale M-line and getting brown, and a narrow triangular marking occurring forward of M-line. Head approximately as wide as the pronotum; compound eyes black; antenna and palpi yellow. Distance between ocelli slightly wider than the diameter of an ocellus. Pronotum disc brown, midline darker, margins pale (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="19F6C544CA590EADA29BF26F72364B0F" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Neoperla gaoligongshana sp. nov. (male) A head and pronotum, dorsal view B adult habitus, dorsal view C terminalia, dorsal view D terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667988" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1B, C</figureCitation>
). Wings subhyaline, veins brown; legs pale to yellowish brown, femorotibial joint dark brown. Abdomen brownish, cerci brownish (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="49BC79B482B786B0F612429AEDCBF747" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Neoperla gaoligongshana sp. nov. (male) A head and pronotum, dorsal view B adult habitus, dorsal view C terminalia, dorsal view D terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667988" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1B, C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="C32F42DD02AB44069A18FE78783AC0AE" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667988" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="7186001DDA0209B1E2F7064216736B40" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="5DDD641B67988037F767820DB3BDCECF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="96D3D2B133F6472115FB5F1B31CEFFF7" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Neoperla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neoperla gaoligongshana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gaoligongshana">
<emphasis id="73A616EB059D199C98C4A5692665A904" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Neoperla gaoligongshana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (male) 
<emphasis id="6AE39E13DCA7A04A73A57541ED552BCE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
head and pronotum, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="127DDD35CE63012E20D7D47665AB908E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
adult habitus, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="D29319EA94A187F50CFF439DB5D5DCAF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C</emphasis>
terminalia, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="E365874EAF670F8716AD07082CFD2BD1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D</emphasis>
terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="691D736C6317AC1869EAFED2086C7D4F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="F42B0BE77FCEE1A5F27658C7393D3066" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="598B08794A28FEF99A2A409A072F6259" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Neoperla gaoligongshana sp. nov. (male) A head and pronotum, dorsal view B adult habitus, dorsal view C terminalia, dorsal view D terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667988" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B9B2C464DBC3D6B79BC538D3C1893E29" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Neoperla gaoligongshana sp. nov. (male) A aedeagus with everted sac, dorsal view B aedeagus with everted sac, ventral view C aedeagus with everted sac, dorsolateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667989" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2</figureCitation>
). Forewing length ca 10.9 mm, hindwing length ca 9.7 mm. Tergum 6 unmodified. Process of tergum 7 triangular, apex rounded and margined by sparse spines (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EA0E845A10F0FE2323D8FEFA223BDFD4" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Neoperla gaoligongshana sp. nov. (male) A head and pronotum, dorsal view B adult habitus, dorsal view C terminalia, dorsal view D terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667988" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1B, D</figureCitation>
). Tergum 8 with a median sensilla basiconica patch on a trapezoidal sclerite. Tergum 9 with two lateral patches of several sensilla basiconica and long hairs. Hemitergal processes slender, straight in lateral aspect, apex obtuse (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3A68227E80762FB65291DDCEA29E072C" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Neoperla gaoligongshana sp. nov. (male) A head and pronotum, dorsal view B adult habitus, dorsal view C terminalia, dorsal view D terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667988" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1B, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC8B1E7A095E6DB5729718A4C48278B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="C9FC1BD93A23075AE237AB3B3D7A9528" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aedeagus</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="551DE61CB25E7839D1C8EBA48577FB40" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Neoperla gaoligongshana sp. nov. (male) A aedeagus with everted sac, dorsal view B aedeagus with everted sac, ventral view C aedeagus with everted sac, dorsolateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667989" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal tube weakly sclerotized ventrally and dorsally sclerotized strongly, apex with two ventral spinous lobes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A4BC150694ED7372C18AB8F584FD1D13" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Neoperla gaoligongshana sp. nov. (male) A aedeagus with everted sac, dorsal view B aedeagus with everted sac, ventral view C aedeagus with everted sac, dorsolateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667989" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2A, B</figureCitation>
). Sac nearly straight, ca 2
<normalizedToken id="EE8539D2C5849BD6A26F12FE91744206" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as the tube. Spinose apex of sac slender, slightly ventrally curved, with an apical dorsolateral patch of black spines and a subapical ventral patch of spines (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6A592C90937FC2048EB1987E02D1553B" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Neoperla gaoligongshana sp. nov. (male) A aedeagus with everted sac, dorsal view B aedeagus with everted sac, ventral view C aedeagus with everted sac, dorsolateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667989" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2A, C</figureCitation>
); two wide rows of numerous smaller spines covering most of the dorsal surface of the sac, basal half of spinous rows interrupted medially (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D192DF69D45B8D17EB26314DD59821F8" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Neoperla gaoligongshana sp. nov. (male) A aedeagus with everted sac, dorsal view B aedeagus with everted sac, ventral view C aedeagus with everted sac, dorsolateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667989" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2A, C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="3FC4FE78769A5D1DCFD713E21B79E88A" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667989" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="6D0A2841B6577EEFCEBA28D3CEAB3513" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="9F5443A24F043A35A64F9FB1CD7CDFF3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="F04032BB4E0AF8C510245360ACFEFB8E" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Neoperla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neoperla gaoligongshana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gaoligongshana">
<emphasis id="31E20A4B49C701F711026874C3D3C37A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Neoperla gaoligongshana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (male) 
<emphasis id="6BD6C2AAF8E44E07D235D2D0C1F3A707" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
aedeagus with everted sac, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="E39E149B8B028F1373F72AE666C46970" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
aedeagus with everted sac, ventral view 
<emphasis id="8ACC03EECB93E01AAAB1A54DD4AE0526" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C</emphasis>
aedeagus with everted sac, dorsolateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="006B0BF7806EF13E5E1FEADC4C2C7B96" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="27D0AD10C1484B2E9310D06BB18F5400" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="794850234AB6ABE13371CBA14C867BAF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="951C81B27A7C08FDC3DC42D77BAD6C5A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CDAE937D598467750D1848517B2EFE49" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The specific name refers to the Gaoligongshan National Nature Reserve in Yunnan Province, where the type locality is situated.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7A99A8569703661C7114496B907D9E33" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6C2069BE7F938F263C3DFA8348AFF8E0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C3582B40CA4F42F0C55050BAFA0E9106" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">China (Yunnan).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C8CE0BC88D36547696F5AAD664D41DF6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="189FB95BC96A3E4B2FC162E0223803F9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A046D7EAC7052D0F1E86E2458C35B192" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Gaoligongshan National Nature Reserve is located in northwestern Yunnan Province and is the largest nature reserve of the province. At the same locality, accompanying stoneflies were 
<taxonomicName id="9343B7AFADC59BAEFBFCB53E062BB71F" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Neoperla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neoperla hajeki" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hajeki">
<emphasis id="7786B029E7A0FAA561F4FA99EBBA2EE8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Neoperla hajeki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. and 
<taxonomicName id="81D641EA81E11300937E97A1F427AFB9" authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Tyloperla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tyloperla illiesi" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="illiesi">
<emphasis id="CD84796E40D9747A195A281E12C4DC5D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Tyloperla illiesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stark &amp; Sivec, 2005.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5AC667AD6D81C2FAF919AC4D294DA701" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="D99B4F86CB310788DE7216E8C0D2C609" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5CBB4B4AB9A807324709279AD1BCBD4A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The new species is a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="530F925782862666132A85D1F074A957" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. montivaga" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montivaga">
<emphasis id="CE0D390BF2EDB6B6D9D76F3964B0002F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. montivaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The aedeagal tube and terga 7-10 of the new species are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="922787E0538C552F293DB053FC3E1967" authorityName="Chen &amp; Y. Du" authorityYear="2016" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Neoperla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neoperla wuzhishana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wuzhishana">
<emphasis id="31BE8A63625137DE9B976AC82568D9B5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Neoperla wuzhishana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chen &amp; Du, 2016, but 
<taxonomicName id="0A9C8EF221312D7B0D1806C8BC7F505E" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. wuzhishana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wuzhishana">
<emphasis id="8460043E8DC82085D8EDAAFFCDB2BAC7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. wuzhishana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the new species primarily by the shape of the aedeagal sac and aedeagal armatures (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E36EB0823B8FD1701139F7BDB7BA6FEF" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Neoperla wuzhishana Chen &amp; Du, 2016 (A, C-E male B female), all from Yinggeling, Hainan Province A head and pronotum, dorsal view B head and pronotum, dorsal view C Aedeagus, lateral view D Large spines of aedeagal sac, ventral view E legs, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C, E); 0.1 mm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667995" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8C</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="8F18A335A7E30EF9C6F9AC584E152E87" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. wuzhishana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wuzhishana">
<emphasis id="197768A1345A4FAC35ECB6C842C44B36" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. wuzhishana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the aedeagal sac is distinctly curved and expanded apically (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3EF81397E67D21D70AB4C4DA45402453" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Neoperla wuzhishana Chen &amp; Du, 2016 (A, C-E male B female), all from Yinggeling, Hainan Province A head and pronotum, dorsal view B head and pronotum, dorsal view C Aedeagus, lateral view D Large spines of aedeagal sac, ventral view E legs, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C, E); 0.1 mm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667995" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8C</figureCitation>
, present study) (which is obscure in the original drawing because of an apical damage in the type) and has at least four large dorsal spines subapically (see figs 7, 8 in 
<bibRefCitation id="FD95702893DE01D83F0F4EDB0C027283" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4144.2.6" author="Chen, ZT" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="243 - 252" refId="B3" refString="Chen, ZT, Du, YZ, 2016b. Contribution to the knowledge of Neoperla (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Hainan Province of China. Zootaxa 4144 (2): 243 - 252, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4144.2.6" title="Contribution to the knowledge of Neoperla (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Hainan Province of China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4144.2.6" volume="4144" year="2016 b">Chen, Du 2016b</bibRefCitation>
); however, the aedeagal sac of 
<taxonomicName id="7FFE54592B7309743C6ABDC026523C60" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. gaoligongshana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gaoligongshana">
<emphasis id="78B97A4EE199B1806AC3031147507370" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. gaoligongshana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nearly straight and the apex is constricted and has only small spines subapically on its dorsal side. In addition, the aedeagal sac of 
<taxonomicName id="5A2DB509B5920828D1976E6A26D6929A" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. wuzhishana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wuzhishana">
<emphasis id="6791ADE5378178D69AE3E0F7640D068D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. wuzhishana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears a dozen moderately long spines at mid-length which are absent in 
<taxonomicName id="DA142D40351B65D891797789E1555692" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. gaoligongshana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gaoligongshana">
<emphasis id="D6DC6A70A3F4A66ACC1E87E703D5612E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. gaoligongshana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Besides, the color pattern including that of the head and legs of 
<taxonomicName id="9EC054E3D50F2FE46094E00DF8964DFB" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. wuzhishana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wuzhishana">
<emphasis id="620138CE685796ED2A5B572F3BBAC87B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. wuzhishana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FC308344E9E6D0F555245F8743E16B21" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. gaoligongshana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gaoligongshana">
<emphasis id="F0C1A23C28CED7F247C212DFED6DF3C1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. gaoligongshana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different: 
<taxonomicName id="9CCF2C19F09AA443B63B583774AA1243" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. wuzhishana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wuzhishana">
<emphasis id="CB73E8FF7C04DCF0FA8D359B49ADCF95" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. wuzhishana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has brown legs and the head is pale with a small dark spot between the posterior ocelli, while in 
<taxonomicName id="67F09D68DAB051D38FDA4222D941B7FD" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. gaoligongshana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gaoligongshana">
<emphasis id="543D021E27F55D452FEA9371CFA879F3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. gaoligongshana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the legs are pale to yellowish brown, the femorotibial joint is dark brown, and the head has a large, black marking covering the ocellar triangle, with this marking extending anterolaterally under the pale M-line (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E54F50108BB7DB3833D1CDA54971F763" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Neoperla gaoligongshana sp. nov. (male) A head and pronotum, dorsal view B adult habitus, dorsal view C terminalia, dorsal view D terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667988" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D429E7E274673BD5C0C0723BC7258A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
We examined specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C629C5565E936DE2B3FA8D6607630AB" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. wuzhishana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wuzhishana">
<emphasis id="9F4D38D664DCDD088604F59C5AE0DBD5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. wuzhishana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Yinggeling, Hainan Province, and found slight intraspecific variations of head pattern and armatures of the aedeagal sac: the dark area between ocelli in males was slightly smaller than in females, which in both sexes are quite small (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4063AC50969B692442F079D7ACEF9E9A" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Neoperla wuzhishana Chen &amp; Du, 2016 (A, C-E male B female), all from Yinggeling, Hainan Province A head and pronotum, dorsal view B head and pronotum, dorsal view C Aedeagus, lateral view D Large spines of aedeagal sac, ventral view E legs, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C, E); 0.1 mm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667995" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8A, B</figureCitation>
); four large spines in types (both in the original illustrations and descriptions) (see figs 7, 8 in 
<bibRefCitation id="99E317AA69BAE26A09B26B4DF77A3A55" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4144.2.6" author="Chen, ZT" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="243 - 252" refId="B3" refString="Chen, ZT, Du, YZ, 2016b. Contribution to the knowledge of Neoperla (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Hainan Province of China. Zootaxa 4144 (2): 243 - 252, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4144.2.6" title="Contribution to the knowledge of Neoperla (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Hainan Province of China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4144.2.6" volume="4144" year="2016 b">Chen, Du 2016b</bibRefCitation>
), which can number seven to nine in our specimens (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9991DEA8AA5818A7932ACC458C7D4C15" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Neoperla wuzhishana Chen &amp; Du, 2016 (A, C-E male B female), all from Yinggeling, Hainan Province A head and pronotum, dorsal view B head and pronotum, dorsal view C Aedeagus, lateral view D Large spines of aedeagal sac, ventral view E legs, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C, E); 0.1 mm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667995" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8C, D</figureCitation>
). Therefore, the absence of large aedeagal spines in 
<taxonomicName id="621AA9CA038B63B9A1CAE8F0D86693E7" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. gaoligongshana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gaoligongshana">
<emphasis id="D6F8AC3BD98915D76418C266A15FDDFD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. gaoligongshana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is regarded as a distinguishing character, separating it from 
<taxonomicName id="FDFCC66F246B675B38551EF80CD42383" class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. wuzhishana" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wuzhishana">
<emphasis id="B1E88A5718B651DCD21E302A1A387275" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. wuzhishana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
